o shape a new agenda for the future of the workplace: to transform their individual successes into a normal practice of customized work time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aHours of laborzUnited States. 0aPart-time employmentzUnited States. 0aProfessional employeeszUnited States. 0aWomen employeeszUnited States. 0aWork and familyzUnited States. 4aBusiness (General). 4aLabor History. 4aSociology & Social Science.1 aWhalley, Peter, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150173199040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501731990423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501731990/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles